# Testing Standards

- Write tests alongside implementation, not as an afterthought
- Test behavior and outcomes, not implementation details -- tests should survive refactors
- Cover the happy path, edge cases, and error/failure paths
- Tests should be readable as documentation: a new reader should understand expected behavior from test names and assertions alone
- Run the full relevant test suite before committing; never commit broken tests
- Keep tests fast and independent -- no shared mutable state between tests
- Use descriptive test names that state the scenario and expected outcome (e.g. `test_login_with_expired_token_returns_401`)
- Mock external dependencies (network, filesystem, databases) at boundaries, not deep inside the code
